{"tid":2136088,"cid":18,"subCid":0,"title":"大家今年睇咗咩書？","createTime":"2020-08-02T00:40:20.000Z","updateTime":"2020-08-03T11:34:55.000Z","uid":78390,"like":20,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":34,"replies":[{"pid":"d08317d15e8f63d4c9301cee34db6bc4802585eb","tid":2136088,"uid":78390,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-08-02T00:40:20.000Z","msg":"今年疫情令到我睇返書<br />\n其實睇書幾正 同睇戲有得比<br />\n巴絲打不妨擺底幾本書介紹俾大家<br />\n<br />\nThe fifth dialogue - Plato <br />\nProslogian - Anselm<br />\n異鄉人 - Albert Camus<br />\nNotes from Underground- Fyodoe Dostoevsky <br />\nDialogue concerning natural religion - David Hume<br />\nThe Gay Science (選段）- 尼采<br />\nExistentialism is a humanism - Satre<br />\nFear and trembling- Soren Kierkegaard <br />\nMeditation on first philosophy- Rene Descartes<br />\n<br />\n最近上緊哲學堂 都幾鐘意睇哲學家嘅理論 唔算十分了解 但對神同存在主義呢啲話題都幾有興趣睇 睇完mindblown下又好 定了解下呢啲名人思考方式 處世方式 同對真相嘅追求都非常值得睇<br />\nPlato 嘅 fifth dialogues 同異鄉人都可以先睇下<br />\n<br />\nSubtle art of not giving a fuck - Mark Manson <br />\n<br />\nSelf help book雖然我少睇 不過睇完呢本都學到唔少嘢 起碼係編排人生都幾有用<br />\n<br />\nDune - Frank Herbert (好努力睇緊）<br />\nThe Alchemist- Paulo Coelho <br />\nThe catcher in the rye- J.D Salinger <br />\nMan&rsquo;s search for meaning - Viktor E Frank<br />\nSix of Crows- Leigh Bardugo<br />\nTo kill a mocking bird- Harper Lee<br />\n<br />\n故事書都好鐘意睇 細個寧願睇戲都唔睇書 以加發覺其實雙方都有佢嘅趣味 同埋睇書令我更欣賞電影製作 所以係互相交流嘅媒體<br />\n<br />\n人間失格-太宰治<br />\n挪威的森林- Murakami <br />\n<br />\n日本文學都係開始睇書嘅出發點 日本人其實係咪好慘 睇完都有啲傷心難過"},{"pid":"d11eedeee12297b6985a6e443a8fcc26353f490c","tid":2136088,"uid":360830,"like":5,"dislike":2,"score":3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-02T00:52:28.000Z","msg":"鬼滅之刃 - 吾峠呼世晴"},{"pid":"ee17f845abd79db569de7a450ecbb0f1138b53ec","tid":2136088,"uid":211051,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-08-02T01:00:58.000Z","msg":"感覺上9成以上嘅改編電影都遠遠比唔上原著小說，三百幾頁嘅故事好難濃縮成兩三個鐘，人物深度、故事結構好多都要縮減。<br />\n<br />\n少數出色嘅改編電影好似多數係中短篇改編，例如Shawshank Redemption, Arrival 呢啲，可惜本身未拍電影之前就冇咁出名。電影主要優點都係個配樂，睇書點都睇唔到音樂出黎。"},{"pid":"a037a9d4c205162e8690535f224be8726721c408","tid":2136088,"uid":30831,"like":3,"dislike":1,"score":2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-08-02T01:11:41.000Z","msg":"樓主睇啲書好有文化<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"7cf91fbb6d4aae9740370a1adc89976d35c6cea2","tid":2136088,"uid":78390,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"quote":{"pid":"ee17f845abd79db569de7a450ecbb0f1138b53ec","tid":2136088,"uid":211051,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-08-02T01:00:58.000Z","msg":"感覺上9成以上嘅改編電影都遠遠比唔上原著小說，三百幾頁嘅故事好難濃縮成兩三個鐘，人物深度、故事結構好多都要縮減。<br />\n<br />\n少數出色嘅改編電影好似多數係中短篇改編，例如Shawshank Redemption, Arrival 呢啲，可惜本身未拍電影之前就冇咁出名。電影主要優點都係個配樂，睇書點都睇唔到音樂出黎。"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-08-02T01:12:37.000Z","msg":"電影配合嘅嘢好多 演技拍攝剪接 節奏嘅掌握都比書更難<br />\n<br />\n睇咗書會更多了解角色發展 同佢地內心世界 所以演員要㧓緊角色心理其實真係好難<br />\n<br />\nThe social network 係我覺得由書轉做電視最好作品"},{"pid":"07a66e6d6cf1f2d0a8701ca5bdde5f18fd769e36","tid":2136088,"uid":78390,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"quote":{"pid":"a037a9d4c205162e8690535f224be8726721c408","tid":2136088,"uid":30831,"like":3,"dislike":1,"score":2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-08-02T01:11:41.000Z","msg":"樓主睇啲書好有文化<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-02T01:13:27.000Z","msg":"Lol 都係睇啲經典書以加"},{"pid":"681107e3932a02ed8d95d034bf95c7d561cff5ff","tid":2136088,"uid":22030,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2020-08-02T01:18:49.000Z","msg":"Thinking, Fast and Slow by Daniel Kahneman"},{"pid":"cfbe0e37b6d3613c144afd1bf71d230418d43e13","tid":2136088,"uid":78390,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"681107e3932a02ed8d95d034bf95c7d561cff5ff","tid":2136088,"uid":22030,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2020-08-02T01:18:49.000Z","msg":"Thinking, Fast and Slow by Daniel Kahneman"},"cited